< review>
Great ambiance, room and overall service experience. Nice selection of wines - local and otherwise. Citrus salad was really outstanding. Short rib was tender - flavourful. Pasta with tomato, ricotta and lemon was underwhelming- sounded like an interesting combo but turned out not to be. Waiter offered a replacement or dessert / port. The women behind me also complained about her order of the same dish. Net net we would go back - all the elements of a great experience.

36 State St, Santa Barbara, CA  93101, United States<//review>

< Text>
This was our first visit to Blackbird. We were early at 6pm on a Tuesday and had the place virtually to ourselves. Kelly, our server, could not have been more personable and professional. He described each dish we inquired about as if he were the chef and creator himself. He gave us the right balance of attention and service that complimented the delicious and creative dishes. We recommend the chickpea fries for an app, the diver scallops as the entree, and the most unusual Milk & Cookies for dessert. Don't miss this great new addition to the Hotel Californian complex .<//Text>

<Text>Great feel to this place! Although it may be a bit out of place in lower State, Blackbird has more of an up-town vibe, which may explain why the T-shirt and baseball cap crowd was jamming Finney's across the street, but we walked in and were able to sit at an excellent table. The service was attentive and unobtrusive, the chickpea fries were a great tasting menu item, the wines by the glass were carefully curated and served in the perfect stemware, and the draft beers featured some of my favorite craft beers. This is your place if you could use a little break from "bro" joints.</Text></record>

< Review>
Authentic family run Mexican food restaurant serving scatch-made classic entrees in a humble yet spacious dining room in the heart of Old Town Goleta. The beef alambre was beautifully composed and surprisingly savory with the addition of bacon to the usual ingredients. I can't wait to go back and try the homemade chicken mole.</Review>

< Review>
I have shopped with Mattress Firm (at Steven's Creek) before and we decided to return here to upgrade a king size mattress. It was a little past 7 PM when we arrived. Destiny, the store manager was very helpful and patient with us and walked us through the different options we could pick from. She made us feel comfortable and relaxed and made the experience all the more better. We finally picked a Tempurpedic king which met our budget and comfort needs.

Even though it was a tad beyond closing time, she ensured made sure we were well informed and never pushed us towards any additional purchases.

Delivery:

The mattress was delivered to us in two days and the delivery personnel were extremely quick : Removing / transferring our older mattresses and installing the new one - all within 30 minutes. Social distancing and safety norms followed throughout.

I highly recommend this store for their excellent customer service.< /Review>

< Text>
I will forever feel grateful to the salesperson who assisted me. She possessed a unique blend of abilities and personality. She genuinely seemed to want to assist me even though I told her I probably wouldn't buy anything today. She asked me many questions; side, back, front sleeper etc. so she could help guide my decision. In fact, I was buying the bed for my 6'1" son who was away at college as his childhood bed was too small. She was personable, yet receptive which made me feel comfortable discussing my personal situation. She had excellent product knowledge. In the course of our discussion, I revealed how my son had a congenital heart defect and has had 5 open heart surgeries. She then wondered if a frame with the ability to recline/incline the head and feet would help him rehabilitate after his surgeries.  I had always thought these kinds of beds cost $5,000 and therefore out of the question. I was shocked at the low price. My son suffered greatly after every one of his open heart surgeries when he came home from the hospital to his flat bed. I was very sad that I never knew how affordable these reclining frames were. I do not discuss my personal business with strangers but this lady was different and I will forever feel the most profound sense of gratitude for the rest of my life.  She has helped me and my son more than she will ever know.  Jovannah, you are the best! Thank you!< /Text>

<user_id>101163325899795246125< /user_id><username>Josh Kuhn</username>< date>
1494793541890</date>
< Rating>
5< /Rating>
< review>
I happened to be in SLO for a week-long work trip in late April.  For some reason I had this crazy notion that if I woke up at 5:15am, I could surf in the mornings before heading in to the office at 9.  But where to find a deal on renting a board for an entire week?  The number of surf shops made it an almost overwhelming task.  PBSA came highly recommended by the bartender at Cool Cat Cafe, just down the street.

I stopped by, and explained my crazy idea to Rodney.  He was totally into it.  I didn't think I needed a lesson --which is dumb, you should totally get a lesson if you've never surfed before-- but Rodney hooked me up with a board and some basic advice, and I ran down to the beach,  stoked up like an 8 year old on Christmas morning.

The surfing at Pismo was absolutely fantastic.  On one particularly epic morning I counted 23 other surfers out there with me at 7:30am.  Watching the experienced folks catch waves was super cool.  But even Pismo has bad days, occasionally.  Towards the end of my week-long trip there was a day with a strong southerly current and huge wind-swell.  I fought the surf for a few minutes, but the Ocean was definitely winning.

On the way out, I happened to say hi to one of the locals in the parking lot.  He mentioned that Avila might be better.  After a 15 minute drive north, I discovered a perfectly groomed shore-break firing some very well mannered 3-foot pipes.  Day saved.

Bottom line, bring your crazy self to Pismo Beach Surf Academy.  They've got you covered.<//review>

While we were looking for a brief surfing class on the beach, we encountered coach Rodney and photographer Izzy by chance when they were teaching other students on Pismo.

< review>
Very affordable Salvadorean food with authentic flavors. Nice set up with plenty of spacious tables and the ambiance is really great because the interior is well lit, clean and organized. However my pupusas were pretty greasy. Also i specifically asked for 2 of them to be made with rice instead of the traditional corn masa but alas I got corn even though I paid more. The arrayan and ensalada drinks we had were not bad at all. Definitely worth a second visit i believe...< /review>

< rating>
5<//rating>
< Review>
This place is now one of my favorites to get an authentic pupusas revuelta, pastelitos de carne (meat mixed w/veggies in a bun) and frescos like Ensalada (mixed fruit juice and real fruit served over ice) in the South Bay.  The pastelitos are made to order, served w/curtido (pickled cabbage) and come 2 per order.  The pupusas are made to order as well and served with a distinctive curtido that looked like it was glowing!  It was sooo cool to see that but the best part is biting into that pupusa revuelta w/curtido and salsa de tomate (tomato sauce).   Of course you cannot forget the ENSALADA!!!  With this summer weather it beats the thirst w/an Ensalada over ice!  Next visit I'll definitely try the tamales, SalpicÃ³n, Sopa de Gallina and the Yuca!  Pictures will be posted soon!<//Review>
